Python Learning Resources

Courses

#1 100 Days of Code (Udemy - Paid)

Good amount of lectures and great explantion. Split into daily modules demanding 1 hourish per day. Includes all other libraries and developments like web, game ,etc. too

(https://www.udemy.com/course/100-days-of-code/)

#2 MIT OpenCourseware (Free)

Explained easily and in a beginner friendly pattern by Professors in MIT.

(https://ocw.mit.edu/courses/6-0001-introduction-to-computer-science-and-programming-in-python-fall-2016/)

Online websites

W3Schools (Use as a Text Book)

Provides examples and an online editor to test out code All attributes and elements are explained in detail.

(https://www.w3schools.com/python/default.asp)

Google's Python Class

(https://developers.google.com/edu/python)

Educative's Learn Python3

(https://www.educative.io/courses/learn-python-3-from-scratch)

That's all the online resources I have apart from this, Channels on YT like CodeWithHarry and ProogrammingWithMosh have good courses too
